HEADWORD: Washingtonian
<hw>Wash`ing*to"ni*an</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Pertaining to, or characteristic of, <person>George
<etsep>Washington</etsep></person>; <as>as, a <ex>Washingtonian</ex>
policy</as>.</def> <rj><au>Lowell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Designating, or pertaining to, a temperance society
and movement started in Baltimore in 1840 on the principle of total
abstinence.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A member of the
Washingtonian Society.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Washoe process</ent>⟦br⟧
